  "text": "Although the role of susceptible subgroups will be considered later, Fig. 1 How can the striking differences between the direct estimate from the PNS data and the official estimates of lung cancer risks be explained? The probable scientific reason for this discrepancy is that a small proportion of the population has preexisting genetic damage that renders it extremely vulnerable to low-level ionizing radiation [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
